In a speech at a private residence in Las Vegas, President Biden thanked his supporters and highlighted the progress made during his presidency. He thanked his friends and praised Democratic politicians Dina Titus and Steven Horsford. He mentioned the creation of 12 million new jobs and the reduction of inflation. He also discussed the importance of addressing climate change and passing legislation to combat it. He emphasized the need for infrastructure investment and the creation of manufacturing jobs in the United States. He criticized the Republican Party's opposition to his policies and warned of the consequences of not raising the debt ceiling. He highlighted his administration's efforts to lower drug prices and improve healthcare access. He stressed the importance of investing in education and workforce development. He concluded by expressing optimism about the future of the country and the need to protect democracy.